Body Manager is a body management program designed to measure and track your body fitness via Circle Fitness IBA/InBody 570 and CircleFit wellness app.
Body Fat Percentage is the proportion of fat to the total body weight.
A standardised ratio of weight to height, used as general indicator of health.
The daily minimum level of energy or calories your body requires when at rest (including sleeping) in order to function effectively.
Total Body Water percentage is the total amount of fluid in a person’s body expressed as a percentage of their total weight.
Visceral fat is located deep in the core abdominal area, surrounding and protecting the vital organs.

Body Fat is essential for maintaining body temperature, cushioning joints and protecting internal organs. \/n Too much fat can damage your long-term health. Reducing excess levels of body fat has been shown to directly reduce the risk of certain conditions such as high blood pressure, heart disease, type 2 diabetes and certain cancers. Too little body fat may lead to osteoporosis in later years, irregular periods in women and possible infertility. \/n It is important to check your body fat results against the healthy body fat ranges.
A standardised ratio of weight to height, used as general indicator of health.

Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) is the daily minimum level of energy or calories your body requires when resting, for your respiratory and circulatory organs, neural system, liver, kidneys, and other organs to function effectively.

Water plays a vital role in many of the body\'s processes and is found in every cell, tissue and organ. Maintaining a healthy totaly body water percentage will ensure the body functions efficiently and will reduce the risk of developing associated health problems.

Visceral Fat (Abdominal Fat) is the fat that surrounds the vital organs on the trunk / stomach area of the body. \/n High Visceral Fat levels increase the risk of high blood pressure, heart disease and type 2 diabetes. Lowering Visceral Fat levels can stabilise insulin action substantially, and reduce the risk of diabetes and other related illnesses.
Body Manager works in sync with Circle Fitness IBA or InBody 570.

Physical test contains various standard fitness programs applied by us military to evaluate athlete\'s aerobic capacity and endurance.
This program originally designed for firemen, is used to to monitor heart rate and detect VO2 levels. The program will automatically stop once you reach 85% of your maximum heart rate.
The Cooper test is a distanced physical fitness test designed for the US military. The goal is to see how far one can run in 12 minutes. How far will you go?
The Marine Corps Physical Fitness Test, is a timed 3 mile run. Challenge yourself, and try and finish this run as quickly as possible.
Army Physical Readiness Training test is a timed 2 mile run. Try and complete this course as quickly as possible.
Navy Physical Training test is a timed 1.5 miles run. Try and complete this course as quickly as possible.
Air Force Physical Fitness Test is a timed 1.5 miles run. Try and complete this course as quickly as possible.
This is a timed 1.5 miles run. Try and complete this course as quickly as possible.
